        <div class="row">

            <div class="span5 text-section">
                <strong>Wendy Armstrong Jewett - CEO, Director of Art</strong><br>
                Wendy, primary instigator of AC4C, has been living as an artist and designer her entire life. Her
                parents, and family, all talented and accomplished artists are her greatest inspiration. Wendy would
                admit she is genetically coded to design and create art, and darn little else. Her experience has been
                multifaceted from furniture design and construction, glass casting / etching, stone / steel sculpture,
                lighting design / fabrication, graphic design, drawing and painting. Wendy has, and continues, to
                participate on nonprofit boards, for the arts, environment, and her local community.
            </div>

            <div class="span1 text-section">
            </div>

            <div class="span5 text-section">
                <strong>Jessie Jewett - Director of Fundraising & Events</strong><br>
                Jessie has been organizing fundraisers and events since the age of 6. She has the talent and eye of an
                artist with the ability to apply it to a whole event. When she found there were no Event Planning
                degrees at any Washington Universities she worked with a Communications professor at Western Washington
                University and helped to author and create one. She has worked as a regional Fundraiser/Event Planner
                for a national organization, volunteered for numerous nonprofits, and runs her own Event Planning
                business in Seattle. Her ability to create and oversee our AC4C Fundraising program is integral to our
                goal to be a viable funding source for nonprofits worldwide.
            </div>

